				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12469643#post-4375172</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12469643/scp-4052#post-4375172</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 25 Sep 2019 04:43:35 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Khaim</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1796098</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Kind of ruined by fridge logic: if the sandwich police are capable of understanding and communicating with the Foundation, why didn't they do that immediately?</p> <p>There are many weird-intelligence skips out there, like the buried giant, or that one that kidnaps people to be toll collectors on a tongue. They generally work because they hint that whatever-it-is makes perfect sense from some bizarre alien perspective. The Sandwich Police almost had this, but then they became just another alt-universe SCPF. Kinda like the SPC but with a different shtick, and I don't like the SPC anyways.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
