					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12469643#post-4350693</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12469643/scp-4052#post-4350693</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 04 Sep 2019 14:48:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>T Rutherford</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4620432</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Hah! Good work. The unique responses to the variety of sandwich contraband entering the town really does help build the personality of the anomaly.</p> <p>At first, I was a bit wary of the huge addendum you tacked on, but the allusion to the Foundation itself actually worked quite well. I do agree with peppermint though. A lot of the data from the addendum could be condensed. You take too long to get the point across. Still, cleverly done. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12469643#post-4350625</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12469643/scp-4052#post-4350625</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 04 Sep 2019 14:25:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>peppermint_legos</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5515758</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I love the premise, and the &quot;take it a step further&quot; nature of the narrative. Starts out as a silly bread-cop that steals sandwiches, ends up being so much more.</p> <p>Overall, it was too long for me. The extended logs drag while you read them, but there's a payoff when you &quot;get it.&quot; But after I've gotten it, that the Foundation has been poking something that didn't need poking, I need the article to end. The long letters feel like a speech re-iterating everything about how the Foundation messed up, when it's already very clear they did.</p> <p>Still a great concept and execution. Thanks for this!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
